headline: Ulta Beauty Stock Is Rising. Earnings Strength Was More Than Cosmetic.
summary: Shares of  Ulta Beauty  soared double-digits on Friday after the company posted a strong fiscal first quarter and raised its fiscal-year outlook in the face of macroeconomic uncertainty.  A raft of positive commentary was also driving the stock higher as analysts posited that Ulta was becoming a beauty of a competitor in the industry.  The cosmetics and fragrance retailer reported earnings of $6.70 a share for the quarter ended May 3, handily beating analysts’ calls for $5.81 a share, according to FactSet.
